**Agreement document for DeckFlow Study**   
Researchers: Gregory Croisdale ([gregtc@umich.edu](mailto:gregtc@umich.edu)) and Emily Huang ([emihuang@umich.edu](mailto:emihuang@umich.edu))

In this study, you will engage with DeckFlow, a generative art tool. The study involves using two interfaces: 1\) a card-based interface for simplified user interaction with generative AI, 2\)  a chat-based interface.

The study consists of four phases: a tutorial, hard tasks, soft tasks, and an interview with open access to the tools. You will participate in each phase as described below:

1. Tutorial: You will be introduced to the interfaces and features of DeckFlow through a guided walk-through provided by the researcher.  
2. Hard Tasks: You will be given an existing image and tasked with recreating the image as closely as possible using each of the generative art tools. Each task should take approximately 10 minutes. You will perform one of these tasks per interface.  
3. Soft Tasks: You will be given a prompt (e.g., "create an image of a meal you might find at a food court") and asked to create an image that fits the prompt using each of the generative art tools. Each task should take approximately 10 minutes. You will perform one of these tasks per interface.  
4. Interview with Open Access: After completing the tasks, you will be asked a series of interview questions about your experience using the tools while having free access to each of the tools for demonstration and experimentation.![][image1]

These may be restructured to be performed in a different order.

Between tasks, you'll need to create a few image prompts. This will help us understand if and how your image descriptions evolve with each task.

Throughout the study, you will be asked to think aloud, expressing your thoughts, reactions, and feelings about using the system. At the end of each task, you will be asked to answer a short survey about your experience with the tool. In total, the study is expected to take a maximum of 120 minutes. You will be compensated with a $30 Amazon gift card.

During the study, your voice and your screen while using the tools will be recorded. The data collected will be stored securely and used only for research purposes. The research team will have restricted access to this data, and your personal information will remain confidential. Screen and voice recordings, along with your email information, will be removed from the secure university storage system after the completion of the paper draft (expected within one year).
